        // Each pair of remaining moves (e.g., (1,0) then (-1,0)) can be used to increase diagonal moves.
        // If we are at (X,Y) and need to make 2 more moves:
        // (X,Y) -> (X+1, Y) -> (X+1, Y+1) (1 diagonal, 1 straight)
        // (X,Y) -> (X+1, Y+1) -> (X, Y+1) (1 diagonal, 1 straight)
        // (X,Y) -> (X+1, Y+1) -> (X+2, Y+2) (2 diagonal)
        // (X,Y) -> (X+1, Y+1) -> (X, Y) (1 diagonal, 1 diagonal)
        // The key is that if abs_n and abs_m have the same parity, then (abs_n - abs_m) is even.
        // The parity of the sum of coordinates (abs_n + abs_m) is the same as the parity of k.
        // If (abs_n + abs_m) % 2 == k % 2, then it's possible.
